// Nerf-Ops-Target - README
//
// This was meant to be an easy-to-use Arduino library for detecting "laser" shots from Nerf Ops Alphapoint or Deltaburst guns
// Finally a standalone Arduino sketch decoding Nerf Ops shots and shooting back
//
// README - this file
//
// poc/poc.ino - Proof Of Concept
// simply reads the IR signal from a Sony SBX 1620-52 receiver, decodes the relevant tag and prints out the sender color
// on the serial port
//
// target/target.ino - The target sketch
// drives a RGB LED to indicate its team (RED, BLUE or PURPLE)
// get the IR signal and decodes it
// ackowledges the shot
// shoots back if necessary
//
// protocol.txt - simple description of the decoded tag
//
